  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed air conditioner, by reason of its positioning in close proximity to residential windows and the lack of appropriate acoustic mitigation, would give rise to adverse noise and disturbance impacts, to the detriment of the living conditions of nearby occupiers, contrary to Hackney&#x27;s LP33 Policies LP2 (Development and Amenity) and LP58 (Improving the Environment - Pollution) and London Plan (2021) Policies D13 (Agent of Change) and D14 (Noise).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed rear air conditioner unit, by reason of inappropriate appearance, siting and detailed design would comprise an uncharacteristic, incongruous and unsympathetic addition which would fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the site or the wider Graham Road and Mapledene Conservation Area. As such the proposal is contrary to&amp;nbsp; policy D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan (2021); policy LP1 (Design quality and local character), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) and LP4 (Non Designated Heritage Assets) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009).&lt;/p&gt;"
